content.text:
The `curl` test confirms **Nitro is serving images correctly on localhost:3001**. The problem is in your **Nginx config**.

Your catch-all `location /` block tries to serve from `/var/www/snaptap/ui/profiles/` first, which doesn't have `logo.svg`. Static assets like `/logo.svg`, `/favicon.ico`, `/*.avif` aren't matched by your specific route patterns, so they fall through to the profiles directory.

**Fix:** Add a location block for static assets BEFORE the catch-all:

```nginx
# Static assets from public folder — proxy to Nuxt
location ~* \.(svg|png|jpg|jpeg|gif|ico|webp|avif|woff|woff2|ttf|eot|css|js|json|webmanifest)$ {
    proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:3001;
    proxy_set_header Host $host;
    proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
    proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
    proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
    proxy_cache_bypass $http_upgrade;
}
```

Add this block **after** the `location ^~ /_nuxt/` block and **before** `location = /`.

Then reload Nginx:
```bash
sudo nginx -t && sudo systemctl reload nginx
```

This will route all requests for static file extensions to Node.js, which will serve them from the `public/` directory.
